caffi
=====

caffi is the Channel Access Foreign Function Interface.
It uses CFFI to call EPICS channel access library.

It is the goal of this package to provide direct low level
interface to channel access, alike the C API.

::

    import sys
    import caffi.ca as ca

    context = ca.create_context()

    chid = ca.create_channel('catest')
    status = ca.pend_io(3)
    if status != ca.ECA_NORMAL:
        print(ca.message(status))
        sys.exit(1)

    value = ca.get(chid)
    status = ca.pend_io(3)
    if status != ca.ECA_NORMAL:
        print(ca.message(status))
        sys.exit(1)

    print(value.get())


Install
-------
EPICS libraries have been shipped with the package for Windows, Linux and OS X.
Either use *pip*,
::
    
    $ pip install caffi

or download the source tarball, unzip and run,
::

    $ python setup.py install

